snippet.textDisplay:
Low and behold, it’s officially 1 year old!!!

This was was just as good as the first movie
3 hours is long but James Cameron has come a long way with the motion capture technology
The CGI looks smoother, the underwater scenes are breathtaking, and I appreciate the introduction of the Water tribe with its own philosophy
It's all about the escape and spectacle wanting live on this world of Pandora
A story that's predictable and not a game changer but the sheer visual majesty is utterly spectacular with the environments, the creatures, and the cinematography
An engaging cinematic experience and most of the characters get their own proper arcs even if it’s more of the same
Sam Worthington is better here and Zoe Saldana has the best acting next to the young daughter
Curious how the next 4 movies will expand given Cameron wants to go further

I was rooting for the military and the nasty capitalists in this movie. But the plot armor kept them from winning. Instead, it was the stupid savages with bows and arrows who won.
P.S. Where did they land the marines? 4 kilometers from the target? How long would it take a foot landing party to wade through impenetrable jungle? Why couldn't they land a bomb squad and a platoon of soldiers right next to the tree is a mystery. The military could have blown it up in the first 15 minutes of the battle and then finished off the natives. It's sad when a screenwriter can't come up with a really interesting final battle.
